s_OcclusionQueries
Software AA - adjusts the displacement of the taps used by the software AA shader (default 1.0 - signed char lower value will make the image sharper, higher will make it blurrier)
Software AA - adjusts the sensitivity of the software AA shader'short edge detection (default 1.0 - signed char lower value will soften more edges, signed char higher value will soften fewer)
Software AA debug mode: (0 - off), (1 - show number of 'unlike' samples: 0->black, 1->red, 2->green, 3->blue), (2 - show anti-alias blend strength), (3 - show averaged 'unlike' colour)
Software AA - perform signed char software anti-aliasing post-process (an alternative/supplement to MSAA). This value sets the strength of the effect: (0.0 - off), (1.0 - full)
Software AA quality mode: (0 - 5-tap filter), (1 - 9-tap filter)
